text: Swisscom is Switzerland's leading telecommunications and information technology company. It offers a comprehensive range of services, including mobile and fixed-line telephony, broadband internet, digital television, and various IT services. Headquartered in Ittigen, near Bern, Swisscom has a significant presence in Italy through its subsidiary Fastweb. It is partially owned by the Swiss government, which holds a controlling 51% interest in the company. As of 2023, Swisscom employs approximately 19,729 full-time equivalents and reported revenues exceeding 11 billion CHF.
